## System Overview

Runes are the core customization system replacing a traditional class structure. Each character is built entirely by equipping **Skill Runes** (active abilities) and **Link Runes** (modifiers/supports) without class restrictions.

| Property | Detail |
|---|---|
| Skill Rune shape | Hexagonal; up to 6 link slots around the perimeter |
| Link Rune slot colors | Red, Green, Blue |
| Rune rarities | Normal → Magic → Rare → Legendary |
| Max Link Runes per Skill | Up to 6 (limited by slot count and color match) |
| Runestones | Passive enchantments; up to 3 active at once |
| Link rule | Link Rune color must match the target Skill Rune slot color |
| Channel link | Special Link Runes with a channel tag can bridge two Skill Runes |

---

## Rune Types

| Type | Function | Shape |
|---|---|---|
| **Skill Rune** | Active skill / ability | Hexagonal |
| **Link Rune** | Modifies the linked Skill Rune | Any non-hexagonal |
| **Runestone** | Passive enhancement applied to a Skill Rune in the Rune Cast | Special |

