## Rune Color & Slot Rules

| Color | Primary Attribute | Primary Skill Type |
|---|---|---|
| Red | Strength | Melee, Physical, Fire, Shout |
| Green | Dexterity | Bow, Dagger, Trap, Sentry, Poison |
| Blue | Intelligence | Spell, Elemental, Summon, Totem |

**Rules:**
- A Link Rune can only be placed in a slot whose color matches the Link Rune's color.
- Each Skill Rune has up to 6 slots; the actual slot count and colors vary per rune.
- Slot colors can be changed using **Rune Color Essence** (enchanting material).
- Slot positions can be changed using **Rune Link Essence**.
- New slots can be added using **Rune Birth Essence** (up to max for that rune).
- Two Skill Runes can be chained via a **Channel-tagged Link Rune** linking them in arrow direction order.
- Only one **Convert DMG** Link Rune can be active per Skill Rune at a time.
- Some Link Runes explicitly cannot be combined together (e.g., Persistence disables Crit-based Links).

